# in __main__ block:
# 20+ tests confirming symbolic st_attention aligns with traditional transformer attention:
#   - shape: output shape == input shape (residual-compatible)
#   - causal mask: token i sees exactly tokens [0..i] (autoregressive)
#   - full attention: every token sees all tokens (bidirectional encoder)
#   - padding mask: padded tokens produce zero output, non-padded unaffected
#   - sliding window: each token attends to local window only
#   - diagonal (self-only): each token sees only itself
#   - CLS-token pattern: first token attends to all, others attend to self
#   - cross-attention pattern: query tokens attend to separate key tokens
#   - no attention (all masked): entire output is zero
#   - batch independence: different masks per batch produce independent results
#   - frame ordering: attended tokens appear in positional order (like QK^T @ V)
#   - coefficient semantics: output coeff = number of attended tokens (like attention weight sum)
#   - single token: degenerate case, output = input
#   - content preservation: merge(slice(input)) preserves original text content
#   - monotonic information growth (causal): later tokens carry more info
#   - attention sparsity: sparse mask = fewer frames in output
#   - symmetric mask: symmetric attention = same frames for symmetric tokens
#   - multi-head simulation: independent masks per batch = independent heads
#   - prefix sharing (causal): tokens sharing prefix have shared leading frames
#   - get_causal_attention_mask integration: works with the mask generator
